  "market_context": "On the 4-hour NQ chart, price had run a previous swing low and closed back into the range, producing a displacement move higher. A fair value gap formed and price established a low inside it, setting up the analyst's study of inducement behavior within the bullish leg.",
  "key_observation": "Within a single bullish price leg, two separate inducement moves occurred: price ran a low and closed back above it, then formed another fair value gap and ran a second low, each time continuing higher before ultimately drawing toward buy-side liquidity above.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify that price ran the previous low and closed back into the range, then produced a displacement move higher.",
    "Step 2: Note the fair value gap formed by the displacement, with price putting in a low inside that fair value gap.",
    "Step 3: Observe price moving below that low but not closing below it, followed by continuation higher — first inducement.",
    "Step 4: Identify another fair value gap forming, with another low placed within the gap — second inducement.",
    "Step 5: Note that price is struggling to reach higher, particularly given the strong bullish closes, suggesting price should draw upward toward buy-side liquidity.",
    "Step 6: Confirm that price then expands up into buy-side liquidity, validating the two-inducement read."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price reached up to take buy-side liquidity as anticipated, confirming the two-inducement interpretation of the leg.",
  "lessons": "A single bullish price leg can contain multiple inducement moves — lows ran and reclaimed within fair value gaps. Recognizing how closes respect prior lows reveals continuation intent and helps anticipate the draw toward buy-side liquidity.",
